					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13746907#post-4779002</guid>
				<title>How to Raise a Hero of the Pen</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13746907/scp-5860#post-4779002</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 20 Sep 2020 14:30:38 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Veralta</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6030962</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hello everyone! Veralta's here to present a tale of journalism, 'heroism', free speech, AIs, and virtual worlds, with a hint of a conspiracy within a conspiracy. This is one of the longest skips that I have written (clocking in at 4.9k when I last checked it), but somehow, I made it work.</p> <p>This is also Part 1 of my team's series for the RenCon contest, where we plan to make the Foundation rumble with a brand-new GoI, Aviatica, which is made up of journalists. A massively secret force meets a massive truth-seeking and radical organization, in short.</p> <p>Special thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chiifu" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6394107&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1600653272" alt="chiifu" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6394107)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chiifu" >chiifu</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cerastes" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3352053&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1600653272" alt="Cerastes" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3352053)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cerastes" >Cerastes</a></span> for critting the plot outline and plan for this article, and to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ralliston" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5986843&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1600653272" alt="Ralliston" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5986843)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ralliston" >Ralliston</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sebarus" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2341265&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1600653272" alt="Sebarus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2341265)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sebarus" >Sebarus</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/caspian2" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5343993&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1600653272" alt="caspian2" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5343993)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/caspian2" >caspian2</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/basicskipreader" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6657366&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1600653272" alt="basicskipreader" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6657366)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/basicskipreader" >basicskipreader</a></span> for helping me figure out how to properly do the pacing, tension-building, characterization, motives of said characters, and ending of this article. You guys really helped me out making a story like this :)</p> <p>As always, I hope you enjoy this piece!</p> 
